      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handle rate limits by implementing exponential backoff and monitor response codes like 429 for throttling."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Scaling and Performance Best Practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For high-throughput systems, deploy Chatterbox Aura behind a load balancer with auto-scaling groups. Use connection pooling to minimize latency, and cache frequent queries with a TTL of 300 seconds to reduce model calls. Implement health checks via the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "/health",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " endpoint and set up alerts for error rates above 1%. To optimize costs, batch non-real-time requests and use spot instances where feasible."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Advanced Use Cases and Troubleshooting"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Leverage Chatterbox Aura for complex scenarios like multi-lingual support by adjusting the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "language",
            "code": true
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " header, or integrate with vector databases for retrieval-augmented generation. Common issues include context overflow—mitigate by truncating history with a sliding window—and latency spikes, often resolved by scaling horizontally. Log all API interactions with structured data for auditability, and use distributed tracing to pinpoint bottlenecks in microservices architectures."
          }
        ]
      }
